{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"What is going on"},{"time":2000,"text":"in this baby's mind?"},{"time":4000,"text":"If you'd asked people this 30 years ago,"},{"time":6000,"text":"most people, including psychologists,"},{"time":8000,"text":"would have said that this baby was irrational,"},{"time":11000,"text":"illogical, egocentric --"},{"time":13000,"text":"that he couldn't take the perspective of another person"},{"time":15000,"text":"or understand cause and effect."},{"time":17000,"text":"In the last 20 years,"},{"time":19000,"text":"developmental science has completely overturned that picture."},{"time":22000,"text":"So in some ways,"},{"time":24000,"text":"we think that this baby's thinking"},{"time":26000,"text":"is like the thinking of the most brilliant scientists."}]},{"cues":[{"time":30000,"text":"Let me give you just one example of this."},{"time":32000,"text":"One thing that this baby could be thinking about,"},{"time":35000,"text":"that could be going on in his mind,"},{"time":37000,"text":"is trying to figure out"},{"time":39000,"text":"what's going on in the mind of that other baby."},{"time":42000,"text":"After all, one of the things that's hardest for all of us to do"},{"time":45000,"text":"is to figure out what other people are thinking and feeling."},{"time":48000,"text":"And maybe the hardest thing of all"},{"time":50000,"text":"is to figure out that what other people think and feel"},{"time":53000,"text":"isn't actually exactly like what we think and feel."},{"time":55000,"text":"Anyone who's followed politics can testify"},{"time":57000,"text":"to how hard that is for some people to get."},{"time":60000,"text":"We wanted to know"},{"time":62000,"text":"if babies and young children"},{"time":64000,"text":"could understand this really profound thing about other people."},{"time":67000,"text":"Now the question is: How could we ask them?"},{"time":69000,"text":"Babies, after all, can't talk,"},{"time":71000,"text":"and if you ask a three year-old"},{"time":73000,"text":"to tell you what he thinks,"},{"time":75000,"text":"what you'll get is a beautiful stream of consciousness monologue"},{"time":78000,"text":"about ponies and birthdays and things like that."},{"time":81000,"text":"So how do we actually ask them the question?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":84000,"text":"Well it turns out that the secret was broccoli."},{"time":87000,"text":"What we did -- Betty Rapacholi, who was one of my students, and I --"},{"time":91000,"text":"was actually to give the babies two bowls of food:"},{"time":94000,"text":"one bowl of raw broccoli"},{"time":96000,"text":"and one bowl of delicious goldfish crackers."},{"time":99000,"text":"Now all of the babies, even in Berkley,"},{"time":102000,"text":"like the crackers and don't like the raw broccoli."},{"time":105000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":107000,"text":"But then what Betty did"},{"time":109000,"text":"was to take a little taste of food from each bowl."},{"time":112000,"text":"And she would act as if she liked it or she didn't."},{"time":114000,"text":"So half the time, she acted"},{"time":116000,"text":"as if she liked the crackers and didn't like the broccoli --"},{"time":118000,"text":"just like a baby and any other sane person."},{"time":121000,"text":"But half the time,"},{"time":123000,"text":"what she would do is take a little bit of the broccoli"},{"time":125000,"text":"and go, \"Mmmmm, broccoli."},{"time":128000,"text":"I tasted the broccoli. Mmmmm.\""},{"time":131000,"text":"And then she would take a little bit of the crackers,"},{"time":133000,"text":"and she'd go, \"Eww, yuck, crackers."},{"time":137000,"text":"I tasted the crackers. Eww, yuck.\""},{"time":140000,"text":"So she'd act as if what she wanted"},{"time":142000,"text":"was just the opposite of what the babies wanted."},{"time":145000,"text":"We did this with 15 and 18 month-old babies."},{"time":147000,"text":"And then she would simply put her hand out and say,"},{"time":150000,"text":"\"Can you give me some?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":152000,"text":"So the question is: What would the baby give her,"},{"time":154000,"text":"what they liked or what she liked?"},{"time":156000,"text":"And the remarkable thing was that 18 month-old babies,"},{"time":159000,"text":"just barely walking and talking,"},{"time":161000,"text":"would give her the crackers if she liked the crackers,"},{"time":164000,"text":"but they would give her the broccoli if she liked the broccoli."},{"time":167000,"text":"On the other hand,"},{"time":169000,"text":"15 month-olds would stare at her for a long time"},{"time":171000,"text":"if she acted as if she liked the broccoli,"},{"time":173000,"text":"like they couldn't figure this out."},{"time":176000,"text":"But then after they stared for a long time,"},{"time":178000,"text":"they would just give her the crackers,"},{"time":180000,"text":"what they thought everybody must like."},{"time":182000,"text":"So there are two really remarkable things about this."},{"time":185000,"text":"The first one is that these little 18 month-old babies"},{"time":188000,"text":"have already discovered"},{"time":190000,"text":"this really profound fact about human nature,"},{"time":192000,"text":"that we don't always want the same thing."},{"time":194000,"text":"And what's more, they felt that they should actually do things"},{"time":196000,"text":"to help other people get what they wanted."}]},{"cues":[{"time":199000,"text":"Even more remarkably though,"},{"time":201000,"text":"the fact that 15 month-olds didn't do this"},{"time":204000,"text":"suggests that these 18 month-olds had learned"},{"time":207000,"text":"this deep, profound fact about human nature"},{"time":210000,"text":"in the three months from when they were 15 months old."},{"time":213000,"text":"So children both know more and learn more"},{"time":215000,"text":"than we ever would have thought."},{"time":217000,"text":"And this is just one of hundreds and hundreds of studies over the last 20 years"},{"time":221000,"text":"that's actually demonstrated it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":223000,"text":"The question you might ask though is:"},{"time":225000,"text":"Why do children learn so much?"},{"time":228000,"text":"And how is it possible for them to learn so much"},{"time":230000,"text":"in such a short time?"},{"time":232000,"text":"I mean, after all, if you look at babies superficially,"},{"time":234000,"text":"they seem pretty useless."},{"time":236000,"text":"And actually in many ways, they're worse than useless,"},{"time":239000,"text":"because we have to put so much time and energy"},{"time":241000,"text":"into just keeping them alive."},{"time":243000,"text":"But if we turn to evolution"},{"time":245000,"text":"for an answer to this puzzle"},{"time":247000,"text":"of why we spend so much time"},{"time":249000,"text":"taking care of useless babies,"},{"time":252000,"text":"it turns out that there's actually an answer."},{"time":255000,"text":"If we look across many, many different species of animals,"},{"time":258000,"text":"not just us primates,"},{"time":260000,"text":"but also including other mammals, birds,"},{"time":262000,"text":"even marsupials"},{"time":264000,"text":"like kangaroos and wombats,"},{"time":266000,"text":"it turns out that there's a relationship"},{"time":268000,"text":"between how long a childhood a species has"},{"time":272000,"text":"and how big their brains are compared to their bodies"},{"time":276000,"text":"and how smart and flexible they are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":278000,"text":"And sort of the posterbirds for this idea are the birds up there."},{"time":281000,"text":"On one side"},{"time":283000,"text":"is a New Caledonian crow."},{"time":285000,"text":"And crows and other corvidae, ravens, rooks and so forth,"},{"time":288000,"text":"are incredibly smart birds."},{"time":290000,"text":"They're as smart as chimpanzees in some respects."},{"time":293000,"text":"And this is a bird on the cover of science"},{"time":295000,"text":"who's learned how to use a tool to get food."},{"time":298000,"text":"On the other hand,"},{"time":300000,"text":"we have our friend the domestic chicken."},{"time":302000,"text":"And chickens and ducks and geese and turkeys"},{"time":305000,"text":"are basically as dumb as dumps."},{"time":307000,"text":"So they're very, very good at pecking for grain,"},{"time":310000,"text":"and they're not much good at doing anything else."},{"time":313000,"text":"Well it turns out that the babies,"},{"time":315000,"text":"the New Caledonian crow babies, are fledglings."},{"time":317000,"text":"They depend on their moms"},{"time":319000,"text":"to drop worms in their little open mouths"},{"time":322000,"text":"for as long as two years,"},{"time":324000,"text":"which is a really long time in the life of a bird."},{"time":326000,"text":"Whereas the chickens are actually mature"},{"time":328000,"text":"within a couple of months."},{"time":330000,"text":"So childhood is the reason"},{"time":333000,"text":"why the crows end up on the cover of Science"},{"time":335000,"text":"and the chickens end up in the soup pot."}]},{"cues":[{"time":337000,"text":"There's something about that long childhood"},{"time":340000,"text":"that seems to be connected"},{"time":342000,"text":"to knowledge and learning."},{"time":344000,"text":"Well what kind of explanation could we have for this?"},{"time":347000,"text":"Well some animals, like the chicken,"},{"time":350000,"text":"seem to be beautifully suited"},{"time":352000,"text":"to doing just one thing very well."},{"time":354000,"text":"So they seem to be beautifully suited"},{"time":357000,"text":"to pecking grain in one environment."},{"time":359000,"text":"Other creatures, like the crows,"},{"time":361000,"text":"aren't very good at doing anything in particular,"},{"time":363000,"text":"but they're extremely good"},{"time":365000,"text":"at learning about laws of different environments."}]},{"cues":[{"time":367000,"text":"And of course, we human beings"},{"time":369000,"text":"are way out on the end of the distribution like the crows."},{"time":372000,"text":"We have bigger brains relative to our bodies"},{"time":374000,"text":"by far than any other animal."},{"time":376000,"text":"We're smarter, we're more flexible,"},{"time":378000,"text":"we can learn more,"},{"time":380000,"text":"we survive in more different environments,"},{"time":382000,"text":"we migrated to cover the world and even go to outer space."},{"time":385000,"text":"And our babies and children are dependent on us"},{"time":388000,"text":"for much longer than the babies of any other species."},{"time":391000,"text":"My son is 23."},{"time":393000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":395000,"text":"And at least until they're 23,"},{"time":397000,"text":"we're still popping those worms"},{"time":399000,"text":"into those little open mouths."}]},{"cues":[{"time":402000,"text":"All right, why would we see this correlation?"},{"time":405000,"text":"Well an idea is that that strategy, that learning strategy,"},{"time":409000,"text":"is an extremely powerful, great strategy for getting on in the world,"},{"time":412000,"text":"but it has one big disadvantage."},{"time":414000,"text":"And that one big disadvantage"},{"time":416000,"text":"is that, until you actually do all that learning,"},{"time":419000,"text":"you're going to be helpless."},{"time":421000,"text":"So you don't want to have the mastodon charging at you"},{"time":424000,"text":"and be saying to yourself,"},{"time":426000,"text":"\"A slingshot or maybe a spear might work. Which would actually be better?\""},{"time":430000,"text":"You want to know all that"},{"time":432000,"text":"before the mastodons actually show up."},{"time":434000,"text":"And the way the evolutions seems to have solved that problem"},{"time":437000,"text":"is with a kind of division of labor."},{"time":439000,"text":"So the idea is that we have this early period when we're completely protected."},{"time":442000,"text":"We don't have to do anything. All we have to do is learn."},{"time":445000,"text":"And then as adults,"},{"time":447000,"text":"we can take all those things that we learned when we were babies and children"},{"time":450000,"text":"and actually put them to work to do things out there in the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":453000,"text":"So one way of thinking about it"},{"time":455000,"text":"is that babies and young children"},{"time":457000,"text":"are like the research and development division of the human species."},{"time":460000,"text":"So they're the protected blue sky guys"},{"time":463000,"text":"who just have to go out and learn and have good ideas,"},{"time":465000,"text":"and we're production and marketing."},{"time":467000,"text":"We have to take all those ideas"},{"time":469000,"text":"that we learned when we were children"},{"time":471000,"text":"and actually put them to use."},{"time":473000,"text":"Another way of thinking about it"},{"time":475000,"text":"is instead of thinking of babies and children"},{"time":477000,"text":"as being like defective grownups,"},{"time":479000,"text":"we should think about them"},{"time":481000,"text":"as being a different developmental stage of the same species --"},{"time":483000,"text":"kind of like caterpillars and butterflies --"},{"time":486000,"text":"except that they're actually the brilliant butterflies"},{"time":488000,"text":"who are flitting around the garden and exploring,"},{"time":491000,"text":"and we're the caterpillars"},{"time":493000,"text":"who are inching along our narrow, grownup, adult path."}]},{"cues":[{"time":496000,"text":"If this is true, if these babies are designed to learn --"},{"time":499000,"text":"and this evolutionary story would say children are for learning,"},{"time":502000,"text":"that's what they're for --"},{"time":504000,"text":"we might expect"},{"time":506000,"text":"that they would have really powerful learning mechanisms."},{"time":508000,"text":"And in fact, the baby's brain"},{"time":511000,"text":"seems to be the most powerful learning computer"},{"time":513000,"text":"on the planet."},{"time":515000,"text":"But real computers are actually getting to be a lot better."},{"time":518000,"text":"And there's been a revolution"},{"time":520000,"text":"in our understanding of machine learning recently."},{"time":522000,"text":"And it all depends on the ideas of this guy,"},{"time":525000,"text":"the Reverend Thomas Bayes,"},{"time":527000,"text":"who was a statistician and mathematician in the 18th century."},{"time":530000,"text":"And essentially what Bayes did"},{"time":533000,"text":"was to provide a mathematical way"},{"time":535000,"text":"using probability theory"},{"time":537000,"text":"to characterize, describe,"},{"time":539000,"text":"the way that scientists find out about the world."},{"time":541000,"text":"So what scientists do"},{"time":543000,"text":"is they have a hypothesis that they think might be likely to start with."},{"time":546000,"text":"They go out and test it against the evidence."},{"time":548000,"text":"The evidence makes them change that hypothesis."},{"time":550000,"text":"Then they test that new hypothesis"},{"time":552000,"text":"and so on and so forth."},{"time":554000,"text":"And what Bayes showed was a mathematical way that you could do that."},{"time":557000,"text":"And that mathematics is at the core"},{"time":559000,"text":"of the best machine learning programs that we have now."},{"time":561000,"text":"And some 10 years ago,"},{"time":563000,"text":"I suggested that babies might be doing the same thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":567000,"text":"So if you want to know what's going on"},{"time":569000,"text":"underneath those beautiful brown eyes,"},{"time":571000,"text":"I think it actually looks something like this."},{"time":573000,"text":"This is Reverend Bayes's notebook."},{"time":575000,"text":"So I think those babies are actually making complicated calculations"},{"time":578000,"text":"with conditional probabilities that they're revising"},{"time":581000,"text":"to figure out how the world works."},{"time":583000,"text":"All right, now that might seem like an even taller order to actually demonstrate."},{"time":587000,"text":"Because after all, if you ask even grownups about statistics,"},{"time":589000,"text":"they look extremely stupid."},{"time":591000,"text":"How could it be that children are doing statistics?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":594000,"text":"So to test this we used a machine that we have"},{"time":596000,"text":"called the Blicket Detector."},{"time":598000,"text":"This is a box that lights up and plays music"},{"time":600000,"text":"when you put some things on it and not others."},{"time":603000,"text":"And using this very simple machine,"},{"time":605000,"text":"my lab and others have done dozens of studies"},{"time":607000,"text":"showing just how good babies are"},{"time":609000,"text":"at learning about the world."},{"time":611000,"text":"Let me mention just one"},{"time":613000,"text":"that we did with Tumar Kushner, my student."},{"time":615000,"text":"If I showed you this detector,"},{"time":617000,"text":"you would be likely to think to begin with"},{"time":619000,"text":"that the way to make the detector go"},{"time":621000,"text":"would be to put a block on top of the detector."},{"time":624000,"text":"But actually, this detector"},{"time":626000,"text":"works in a bit of a strange way."},{"time":628000,"text":"Because if you wave a block over the top of the detector,"},{"time":631000,"text":"something you wouldn't ever think of to begin with,"},{"time":634000,"text":"the detector will actually activate two out of three times."},{"time":637000,"text":"Whereas, if you do the likely thing, put the block on the detector,"},{"time":640000,"text":"it will only activate two out of six times."},{"time":644000,"text":"So the unlikely hypothesis"},{"time":646000,"text":"actually has stronger evidence."},{"time":648000,"text":"It looks as if the waving"},{"time":650000,"text":"is a more effective strategy than the other strategy."},{"time":652000,"text":"So we did just this; we gave four year-olds this pattern of evidence,"},{"time":655000,"text":"and we just asked them to make it go."},{"time":657000,"text":"And sure enough, the four year-olds used the evidence"},{"time":660000,"text":"to wave the object on top of the detector."}]},{"cues":[{"time":663000,"text":"Now there are two things that are really interesting about this."},{"time":666000,"text":"The first one is, again, remember, these are four year-olds."},{"time":669000,"text":"They're just learning how to count."},{"time":671000,"text":"But unconsciously,"},{"time":673000,"text":"they're doing these quite complicated calculations"},{"time":675000,"text":"that will give them a conditional probability measure."},{"time":678000,"text":"And the other interesting thing"},{"time":680000,"text":"is that they're using that evidence"},{"time":682000,"text":"to get to an idea, get to a hypothesis about the world,"},{"time":685000,"text":"that seems very unlikely to begin with."},{"time":688000,"text":"And in studies we've just been doing in my lab, similar studies,"},{"time":691000,"text":"we've show that four year-olds are actually better"},{"time":693000,"text":"at finding out an unlikely hypothesis"},{"time":696000,"text":"than adults are when we give them exactly the same task."},{"time":699000,"text":"So in these circumstances,"},{"time":701000,"text":"the children are using statistics to find out about the world,"},{"time":704000,"text":"but after all, scientists also do experiments,"},{"time":707000,"text":"and we wanted to see if children are doing experiments."},{"time":710000,"text":"When children do experiments we call it \"getting into everything\""},{"time":713000,"text":"or else \"playing.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":715000,"text":"And there's been a bunch of interesting studies recently"},{"time":718000,"text":"that have shown this playing around"},{"time":721000,"text":"is really a kind of experimental research program."},{"time":723000,"text":"Here's one from Cristine Legare's lab."},{"time":726000,"text":"What Cristine did was use our Blicket Detectors."},{"time":729000,"text":"And what she did was show children"},{"time":731000,"text":"that yellow ones made it go and red ones didn't,"},{"time":733000,"text":"and then she showed them an anomaly."},{"time":736000,"text":"And what you'll see"},{"time":738000,"text":"is that this little boy will go through five hypotheses"},{"time":741000,"text":"in the space of two minutes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":744000,"text":"(Video) Boy: How about this?"},{"time":748000,"text":"Same as the other side."}]},{"cues":[{"time":751000,"text":"Alison Gopnik: Okay, so his first hypothesis has just been falsified."}]},{"cues":[{"time":760000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":762000,"text":"Boy: This one lighted up, and this one nothing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":765000,"text":"AG: Okay, he's got his experimental notebook out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":771000,"text":"Boy: What's making this light up."},{"time":776000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":785000,"text":"I don't know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":787000,"text":"AG: Every scientist will recognize that expression of despair."}]},{"cues":[{"time":791000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":794000,"text":"Boy: Oh, it's because this needs to be like this,"},{"time":800000,"text":"and this needs to be like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":802000,"text":"AG: Okay, hypothesis two."}]},{"cues":[{"time":805000,"text":"Boy: That's why."},{"time":807000,"text":"Oh."}]},{"cues":[{"time":809000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":814000,"text":"AG: Now this is his next idea."},{"time":816000,"text":"He told the experimenter to do this,"},{"time":818000,"text":"to try putting it out onto the other location."},{"time":822000,"text":"Not working either."}]},{"cues":[{"time":827000,"text":"Boy: Oh, because the light goes only to here,"},{"time":831000,"text":"not here."},{"time":834000,"text":"Oh, the bottom of this box"},{"time":837000,"text":"has electricity in here,"},{"time":839000,"text":"but this doesn't have electricity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":841000,"text":"AG: Okay, that's a fourth hypothesis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":843000,"text":"Boy: It's lighting up."},{"time":845000,"text":"So when you put four."},{"time":851000,"text":"So you put four on this one to make it light up"},{"time":854000,"text":"and two on this one to make it light up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":856000,"text":"AG: Okay,there's his fifth hypothesis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":858000,"text":"Now that is a particularly --"},{"time":861000,"text":"that is a particularly adorable and articulate little boy,"},{"time":864000,"text":"but what Cristine discovered is this is actually quite typical."},{"time":867000,"text":"If you look at the way children play, when you ask them to explain something,"},{"time":870000,"text":"what they really do is do a series of experiments."},{"time":873000,"text":"This is actually pretty typical of four year-olds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":876000,"text":"Well, what's it like to be this kind of creature?"},{"time":879000,"text":"What's it like to be one of these brilliant butterflies"},{"time":882000,"text":"who can test five hypotheses in two minutes?"},{"time":885000,"text":"Well, if you go back to those psychologists and philosophers,"},{"time":888000,"text":"a lot of them have said"},{"time":890000,"text":"that babies and young children were barely conscious"},{"time":892000,"text":"if they were conscious at all."},{"time":894000,"text":"And I think just the opposite is true."},{"time":896000,"text":"I think babies and children are actually more conscious than we are as adults."},{"time":899000,"text":"Now here's what we know about how adult consciousness works."},{"time":902000,"text":"And adults' attention and consciousness"},{"time":904000,"text":"look kind of like a spotlight."},{"time":906000,"text":"So what happens for adults"},{"time":908000,"text":"is we decide that something's relevant or important,"},{"time":910000,"text":"we should pay attention to it."},{"time":912000,"text":"Our consciousness of that thing that we're attending to"},{"time":914000,"text":"becomes extremely bright and vivid,"},{"time":917000,"text":"and everything else sort of goes dark."},{"time":919000,"text":"And we even know something about the way the brain does this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":922000,"text":"So what happens when we pay attention"},{"time":924000,"text":"is that the prefrontal cortex, the sort of executive part of our brains,"},{"time":927000,"text":"sends a signal"},{"time":929000,"text":"that makes a little part of our brain much more flexible,"},{"time":931000,"text":"more plastic, better at learning,"},{"time":933000,"text":"and shuts down activity"},{"time":935000,"text":"in all the rest of our brains."},{"time":937000,"text":"So we have a very focused, purpose-driven kind of attention."},{"time":941000,"text":"If we look at babies and young children,"},{"time":943000,"text":"we see something very different."},{"time":945000,"text":"I think babies and young children"},{"time":947000,"text":"seem to have more of a lantern of consciousness"},{"time":949000,"text":"than a spotlight of consciousness."},{"time":951000,"text":"So babies and young children are very bad"},{"time":954000,"text":"at narrowing down to just one thing."},{"time":957000,"text":"But they're very good at taking in lots of information"},{"time":960000,"text":"from lots of different sources at once."},{"time":962000,"text":"And if you actually look in their brains,"},{"time":964000,"text":"you see that they're flooded with these neurotransmitters"},{"time":967000,"text":"that are really good at inducing learning and plasticity,"},{"time":969000,"text":"and the inhibitory parts haven't come on yet."},{"time":972000,"text":"So when we say that babies and young children"},{"time":974000,"text":"are bad at paying attention,"},{"time":976000,"text":"what we really mean is that they're bad at not paying attention."},{"time":980000,"text":"So they're bad at getting rid"},{"time":982000,"text":"of all the interesting things that could tell them something"},{"time":984000,"text":"and just looking at the thing that's important."},{"time":986000,"text":"That's the kind of attention, the kind of consciousness,"},{"time":989000,"text":"that we might expect"},{"time":991000,"text":"from those butterflies who are designed to learn."}]},{"cues":[{"time":993000,"text":"Well if we want to think about a way"},{"time":995000,"text":"of getting a taste of that kind of baby consciousness as adults,"},{"time":999000,"text":"I think the best thing is think about cases"},{"time":1001000,"text":"where we're put in a new situation that we've never been in before --"},{"time":1004000,"text":"when we fall in love with someone new,"},{"time":1006000,"text":"or when we're in a new city for the first time."},{"time":1009000,"text":"And what happens then is not that our consciousness contracts,"},{"time":1011000,"text":"it expands,"},{"time":1013000,"text":"so that those three days in Paris"},{"time":1015000,"text":"seem to be more full of consciousness and experience"},{"time":1017000,"text":"than all the months of being"},{"time":1019000,"text":"a walking, talking, faculty meeting-attending zombie back home."},{"time":1023000,"text":"And by the way, that coffee,"},{"time":1025000,"text":"that wonderful coffee you've been drinking downstairs,"},{"time":1027000,"text":"actually mimics the effect"},{"time":1029000,"text":"of those baby neurotransmitters."},{"time":1031000,"text":"So what's it like to be a baby?"},{"time":1033000,"text":"It's like being in love"},{"time":1035000,"text":"in Paris for the first time"},{"time":1037000,"text":"after you've had three double-espressos."},{"time":1039000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1042000,"text":"That's a fantastic way to be,"},{"time":1044000,"text":"but it does tend to leave you waking up crying at three o'clock in the morning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1048000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1051000,"text":"Now it's good to be a grownup."},{"time":1053000,"text":"I don't want to say too much about how wonderful babies are."},{"time":1055000,"text":"It's good to be a grownup."},{"time":1057000,"text":"We can do things like tie our shoelaces and cross the street by ourselves."},{"time":1060000,"text":"And it makes sense that we put a lot of effort"},{"time":1062000,"text":"into making babies think like adults do."},{"time":1066000,"text":"But if what we want is to be like those butterflies,"},{"time":1069000,"text":"to have open-mindedness, open learning,"},{"time":1072000,"text":"imagination, creativity, innovation,"},{"time":1074000,"text":"maybe at least some of the time"},{"time":1076000,"text":"we should be getting the adults"},{"time":1078000,"text":"to start thinking more like children."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1080000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}